The paper discusses the state-of-the-art of food recommender systems, which involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for recommending food items, as well as human-computer interaction (HC) considerations for designing user-friendly interfaces. The paper also mentions natural language processing (CL) as a potential area of research for improving food recommendation systems. Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of designing food recommender systems for different user groups (CY) and promoting healthy eating (SI).
